  <pageTitle>Sharpstown High School Demolition, April-May 2018</pageTitle>
  <pageCreated>May 20, 2018</pageCreated>
  <lastUpdated>May 20, 2018</lastUpdated>
  <photosTaken></photosTaken>
  <text>
    <![CDATA[
    <p>
    I'm a 1985 graduate of Sharpstown High School. The original Sharpstown High School building opened in September 1969 with its first graduating class in 1970. Of course, the first Apollo moon landing took place in July 1969, and it was the inspiration for the school theme/mascot.
    </p>
    <p>
     In Houston, it's not uncommon for buildings less then 50 years old to be demolished. The original school building reached the age of 49 before it succumbed to demolition in 2018. The replacement school opened in early 2018. It has a much nicer main hall/mall, and of course is designed to modern standards.
    </p>
    <p>
    If you are a graduate of Sharpstown High School, these photos may bring back some memories - maybe good, or maybe bad. But the building is gone forever, and the site is now a parking lot.
    </p>

    ]]>
</text>
